{"title":"Mondraker Raze 130mm travel do-it-all Trail Bike is MIND telemetry equipped","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/26/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-do-it-all-trail-bike-is-mind-telemetry-equipped/","date":1635256858000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25080636/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-1.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25080636/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-1-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze 130mm travel carbon mtb trail bike\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25080636/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25080636/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25080636/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25080636/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25080636/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25080636/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-1.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276042\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Mondraker are asking you to raise your expectations of what a 130mm travel trail bike can manage with the release of the all-new Mondraker Raze. It rolls up with a trail-specific kinematic promising the pedaling efficiency of an XC bike combined with the downhill capabilities of an enduro bike; quiver killer territory. The bike combines a Stealth Air Full Carbon Frame with Mondraker’s own on-board MIND telemetry system in a bid to deliver the best possible ride feel, <em>almost</em> straight off the bat.</p><div id=\"attachment_276056\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060912/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-HERO-SHOT.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276056\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060912/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-HERO-SHOT.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze 130mm travel mtb side view\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060912/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-HERO-SHOT.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060912/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-HERO-SHOT-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060912/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-HERO-SHOT-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060912/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-HERO-SHOT-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060912/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-HERO-SHOT-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060912/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-HERO-SHOT-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276056\">Mondraker’s ZERO Suspension Platform leaves heaps of room inside the front triangle for a full size water bottle and accessory mounting</p></div><h2>Mondraker Raze</h2><div id=\"attachment_276051\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060855/mondraker-raze-130mm-full-suspension-mountain-bike.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276051\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060855/mondraker-raze-130mm-full-suspension-mountain-bike.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze 150mm fork\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060855/mondraker-raze-130mm-full-suspension-mountain-bike.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060855/mondraker-raze-130mm-full-suspension-mountain-bike-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060855/mondraker-raze-130mm-full-suspension-mountain-bike-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060855/mondraker-raze-130mm-full-suspension-mountain-bike-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060855/mondraker-raze-130mm-full-suspension-mountain-bike-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060855/mondraker-raze-130mm-full-suspension-mountain-bike-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276051\">What looks like a mini-fender forms part of the MIND telemetry system that gathers data on suspension behaviour as you ride</p></div><p>Mondraker say the new Raze takes the best of the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/05/25/mondraker-f-podium-rr-rethinks-aggressive-geometry-in-short-link-xc-race-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">F-Podium XC Bike</a>, and the best of the Foxy Carbon Enduro Bike, combining them into a 130mm travel Trail Bike that will perform up and down. This 29er gets the sleek, drawn-out silhouette typical of a Mondraker with the long top tube translating to that generously large cockpit we’ve come to expect from the Spanish brand’s Forward Geometry design philosophy.&nbsp;</p><div id=\"attachment_276059\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060922/mondraker-raze-carbon-monoblock-upper-link.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276059\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060922/mondraker-raze-carbon-monoblock-upper-link.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze 130mm travel carbon rocker\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060922/mondraker-raze-carbon-monoblock-upper-link.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060922/mondraker-raze-carbon-monoblock-upper-link-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060922/mondraker-raze-carbon-monoblock-upper-link-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060922/mondraker-raze-carbon-monoblock-upper-link-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060922/mondraker-raze-carbon-monoblock-upper-link-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060922/mondraker-raze-carbon-monoblock-upper-link-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276059\">The Monobloc rocker is a one-piece carbon fibre design; the lower link is optimised for increased stiffness as compared to the lower link on previous iterations of the ZERO Suspension Platform</p></div><p>The 130mm rear end is paired with a 150mm travel fork, with all models benefiting from Mondraker’s proprietary integrated telemetry system; <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/09/mondraker-mind-integrated-telemetry-tool-perfects-easy-intuitive-suspension-setup/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MIND</a>. This is a very attractive feature of Mondraker bikes, tech they developed over three years of testing with their World Cup Downhill riders. What was once an expensive and complex piece of technology, both to fit and understand, is now a seamlessly integrated device designed to be understandable by all riders, not just those with a degree in engineering.</p><div id=\"attachment_276055\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060908/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-heaDTUBE.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276055\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060908/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-heaDTUBE.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze mind telemetry suspension technology sensors\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060908/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-heaDTUBE.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060908/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-heaDTUBE-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060908/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-heaDTUBE-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060908/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-heaDTUBE-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060908/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-heaDTUBE-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060908/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-heaDTUBE-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276055\">The bike benefits from Mondraker’s Hidden Housing Guide cable routing, with the rear brake hose, dropper post and gear cables fed through the headset for a neat aesthetic that maximizes the clean-cut lines of the frame; this means no adjustable head tube cups, however.</p></div><p>Sensors on the fork and rocker of the Zero Suspension linkage gather data on travel usage 100 times per second; they do this by measuring the magnetic field from magnets on the left fork leg and swingarm main pivot, respectively.</p><div id=\"attachment_276054\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060905/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-cornering.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276054\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060905/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-cornering.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze 130mm travel trail bike carbon 29er\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060905/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-cornering.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060905/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-cornering-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060905/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-cornering-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060905/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-cornering-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060905/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-cornering-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060905/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-cornering-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276054\">All models of the Raze have a shock with a light compression tune and ultralight rebound tune, with 0.6 volume spacers pre-installed</p></div><p>Unlike the 2022 Mondraker Foxy Carbon, geometry is fixed. Available in sizes S-XL, reach figures extend from 455mm to 515mm within that range, with each frame size sporting 435mm chainstays. A 150mm travel fork gives the Raze a 65.5° head tube angle paired with a 76.5° seat tube angle, with the bottom bracket sitting 30mm below the dropouts at a height of 343mm.</p><div id=\"attachment_276053\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060901/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-COCKPIT.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276053\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060901/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-COCKPIT.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze mtb\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060901/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-COCKPIT.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060901/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-COCKPIT-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060901/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-COCKPIT-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060901/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-COCKPIT-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060901/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-COCKPIT-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060901/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-COCKPIT-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276053\">All models come with a dropper seat post; S: 125mm, M: 150mm, L/XL: 175mm</p></div><div id=\"attachment_276065\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25062657/mondraker-raze-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276065\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25062657/mondraker-raze-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze geometry chart\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1075\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25062657/mondraker-raze-geometry-chart.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25062657/mondraker-raze-geometry-chart-297x200.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25062657/mondraker-raze-geometry-chart-800x538.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25062657/mondraker-raze-geometry-chart-120x81.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25062657/mondraker-raze-geometry-chart-768x516.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25062657/mondraker-raze-geometry-chart-1536x1032.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276065\">2022 Mondraker Raze Geometry Chart for Sizes S-XL</p></div><div id=\"attachment_276130\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25134505/mondraker-raze-fidlock-pocket-water-bottle-mount.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276130\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25134505/mondraker-raze-fidlock-pocket-water-bottle-mount.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze fidlock pocket water bottle mount\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25134505/mondraker-raze-fidlock-pocket-water-bottle-mount.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25134505/mondraker-raze-fidlock-pocket-water-bottle-mount-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25134505/mondraker-raze-fidlock-pocket-water-bottle-mount-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25134505/mondraker-raze-fidlock-pocket-water-bottle-mount-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25134505/mondraker-raze-fidlock-pocket-water-bottle-mount-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25134505/mondraker-raze-fidlock-pocket-water-bottle-mount-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276130\">Credit: Pete Drew</p></div><p>The downtube of the Raze features a Fidlock pocket. The image on the top left shows how the frame is shipped with a plate for mounting a regular water bottle. The plate can however be switched out for a Fidlock mounting plate; the downtube recess simply allows the mount to sit flush with the frame so that a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/06/08/fidlock-cageless-water-bottle-mount-twists-new-design/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Fidlock water bottle</a> can sit lower on the frame, leaving more clearance for larger bottles. Mondraker will be selling branded Fidlock water bottles with the mounting plate.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25073131/mondraker-raze-chainstays.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25073131/mondraker-raze-chainstays.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze chainstays\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25073131/mondraker-raze-chainstays.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25073131/mondraker-raze-chainstays-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25073131/mondraker-raze-chainstays-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25073131/mondraker-raze-chainstays-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25073131/mondraker-raze-chainstays-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25073131/mondraker-raze-chainstays-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The Raze frame is built around a boost rear end, protected at the downtube and chainstays with custom frame protectors, also designed to minimize noise.</p><div id=\"attachment_276057\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060915/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-SHOCK-MUD-GUARD.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276057\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060915/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-SHOCK-MUD-GUARD.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze shock mud guard\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060915/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-SHOCK-MUD-GUARD.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060915/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-SHOCK-MUD-GUARD-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060915/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-SHOCK-MUD-GUARD-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060915/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-SHOCK-MUD-GUARD-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060915/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-SHOCK-MUD-GUARD-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060915/mondraker-raze-130mm-travel-mtb-SHOCK-MUD-GUARD-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276057\">Additional protection is bolted onto the rear of the seat tube to protect the shock from trail debris</p></div><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>Initially, Mondraker are offering the Raze in three full carbon models only; the Raze RR SL, RR, and R. All seem to be appropriately spec’d for reasonably aggressive trail riding with 4-piston brakes , 60 TPI EXO Casing Maxxis rear tires, dropper seat posts and chain guides.</p><div id=\"attachment_276061\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060929/MONDRAKER-RAZE-R.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276061\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060929/MONDRAKER-RAZE-R.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze r black\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060929/MONDRAKER-RAZE-R.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060929/MONDRAKER-RAZE-R-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060929/MONDRAKER-RAZE-R-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060929/MONDRAKER-RAZE-R-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060929/MONDRAKER-RAZE-R-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060929/MONDRAKER-RAZE-R-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276061\">The Mondraker Raze R model weighs a claimed 13.2 kg in size medium</p></div><p>At the cheaper end of the spectrum (not exactly “budget”), the Raze R retails at £5,499. For that money you get a FOX 36 Float EVOL Performance fork with GRIP damper and a FLOAT DPS LV EVOL Performance shock delivering 150mm and 130mm of suspension travel, respectively. It rolls on a DT SWISS XM1700 SPLINE alloy wheelset with DT 350 hubset. Other highlights include SRAM G2 brakes and SRAM GX Eagle derailleur shifting through the 10-52T cassette.</p><div id=\"attachment_276062\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060932/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276062\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060932/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker raze rr\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060932/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060932/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060932/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060932/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060932/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060932/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276062\">The Mondraker Raze RR model weighs a claimed 12.5 kg in size medium</p></div><p>Next up is the £6,799 Mondraker Raze RR, upgraded with the GRIP2 damper of the Factory level FOX 36, and the DPS Factory shock. Other highlights include the SRAM G2 RS brakes, SRAM X1 carbon crankset and XO1 Eagle derailleur.</p><div id=\"attachment_276063\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060936/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-SL.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276063\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060936/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-SL.jpg\" alt=\"MONDRAKER RAZE RR SL\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060936/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-SL.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060936/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-SL-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060936/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-SL-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060936/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-SL-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060936/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-SL-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25060936/MONDRAKER-Raze-RR-SL-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276063\">The Mondraker Raze RR SL models weighs a claimed 12.2 kg in size medium</p></div><p>Topping the range is the Raze RR SL, priced at £9,299. This one also gets the FOX 36 Factory fork with GRIP2 damper, though the FIT4 is shown above. The shock is the DPS Factory Kashima model with 3-position compression lever and rebound adjustment. The main upgrades include the DT SWISS XCM1200 Carbon SPLINE wheelset with DT 240 hubset, SRAM G2 RSC brakes, SRAM XO1 Carbon Crankset, and AXS Eagle electronic shift drivetrain, as well as the AXS Reverb dropper seat post.</p><p><a href=\"https://mondraker.com/es/en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Mondraker.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"84e64d256d5256a8abdce95109d2094adae4b9b28cab59eb357afdfc10e49b6e","category":"Cycling"}